PAM clustering

SinoVac

for (k in 1:20) { 
  if (k==1) {
    nclusters[k]=NA
    silhouette[k]=NA
  } else {
    data.cluster_temp=pam.clustering(data.dist, k)
    nclusters[k]=index.G1(species.data.d0.snv.all,data.cluster_temp,  d = data.dist,
                          centrotypes = "medoids")
    silhouette[k]=mean(silhouette(data.cluster_temp, data.dist)[,3])
  }
}

Extended Data Figure 9a: CH index

ch.df <- data.frame(n_cluster=c(1:length(nclusters)),
                    ch_index=nclusters)

  xlab("Number of clusters") + ylab("Calinski-Harabasz index ") +
